150 grams Jasmine Rice
80 grams Green Beans
240 grams British Beef Mince
45 grams Yellow Thai Style Paste
15 milliliter(s) Soy Sauce
30 grams Peanut Butter
25 grams Ketjap Manis
15 grams Honey
25 grams Salted Peanuts
150 milliliter(s) Water for the Sauce

Boil a half-full kettle. Pour it into a saucepan with 1/4 tsp salt on high heat.
Boil the rice, 10-12 mins.
Once cooked, drain, pop back in the pan and cover.
Meanwhile, trim the green beans and cut into thirds.

Heat a drizzle of oil in a frying pan on high heat.
Once hot, fry the beef mince and green beans, 5-6 mins. Break up the mince as it cooks.
Meanwhile, open the remaining sachets.
Drain the fat from the mince. Season with salt and pepper. IMPORTANT: Wash hands and equipment after handling raw mince. Cook so there's no pink in the middle.

Add the yellow Thai style paste, soy, peanut butter, ketjap manis, honey and water for the sauce (see pantry) to the pan. Stir well.
Simmer, 3-4 mins.

Share your rice between bowls.
Top with the stir-fry.
Sprinkle over the peanuts to finish.
Enjoy!